==Abstract==

This IIP specifies onion routing for Lightning payments, adapted from BOLT #4 to use ML-KEM-1024 (Kyber1024).

==Motivation==

Onion routing provides:
* Sender privacy
* Recipient privacy
* Path privacy
* Atomic payments

==Specification==

===Onion Packet Structure===

<pre>
+----------------+------------------+---------------------+
| Version (1)    | Ephemeral PK     | Encrypted Payload   |
| 0x00           | (1568 bytes)     | (2000 bytes)        |
+----------------+------------------+---------------------+
| HMAC (32 bytes)                                        |
+--------------------------------------------------------+
Total: 4096 bytes
</pre>

===Key Encapsulation===

Uses Kyber1024 KEM instead of ECDH:

<pre>
// Sender
KyberEncapsulate(hop_pubkey, shared_secret, ciphertext)

// Recipient
KyberDecapsulate(hop_privkey, ciphertext, shared_secret)
</pre>

===Per-Hop Payload===

{| class="wikitable"
|-
! Type !! Length !! Description
|-
| 2 || 8 || amt_to_forward
|-
| 4 || 4 || outgoing_cltv_value
|-
| 6 || 8 || short_channel_id
|-
| 8 || var || payment_data (final hop)
|}

===Encryption===

<pre>
rho = SHAKE256(shared_secret || "rho")
mu = SHAKE256(shared_secret || "mu")

ChaCha20Poly1305Encrypt(rho, nonce, payload)
hmac = HMAC_SHA3_256(mu, encrypted_payload)
</pre>

===INTcoin vs Bitcoin===

{| class="wikitable"
|-
! Property !! BOLT #4 !! IIP-53
|-
| Key size || 33 bytes || 1568 bytes
|-
| Packet size || 1366 bytes || 4096 bytes
|-
| Security || Pre-quantum || Post-quantum
|}

